This paper is about improving the quality of open-domain spoken dialog systems using automatic conversation evaluators. The paper discusses the use of encoder-decoder based neural architectures, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning, and focuses on improving the coherence and engagement of the responses generated by these systems. Given the focus on natural language processing and machine learning, as well as the use of neural architectures, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Sound), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper also discusses the importance of incorporating explicit feedback into the response generation models to improve the quality of the dialog system.
